(2, 'Inception', 'A thief who steals secrets through dream-sharing technology is given a final job: plant an idea in someone''s mind.', 'Dreams within dreams within dreams. When you''re elevated, the layers make more sense and less sense simultaneously. The rotating hallway fight hits different.', '{"year": 2010, "director": "Christopher Nolan", "genre": "Sci-Fi Thriller", "where_to_watch": "Max, Amazon Prime"}', 1),
(2, 'Interstellar', 'Astronauts travel through a wormhole seeking a new home for humanity as Earth becomes uninhabitable.', 'The time dilation scenes and fifth-dimensional tesseract will blow your mind. Cannabis helps you sit with the cosmic scale and emotional weight.', '{"year": 2014, "director": "Christopher Nolan", "genre": "Sci-Fi Drama", "where_to_watch": "Paramount+, Amazon Prime"}', 2),
(2, 'The Matrix', 'A hacker discovers that reality is a simulation and joins a rebellion against the machines.', 'The ultimate stoner movie. "What is real?" hits harder when you''re questioning your own perception. The bullet-time effects are iconic for a reason.', '{"year": 1999, "director": "Wachowski Sisters", "genre": "Sci-Fi Action", "where_to_watch": "Max, Amazon Prime"}', 3),
(2, 'Memento', 'A man with short-term memory loss uses notes and tattoos to hunt for his wife''s killer.', 'The reverse chronology matches the protagonist''s confusion. When elevated, you experience his disorientation firsthand. Multiple viewings reveal new connections.', '{"year": 2000, "director": "Christopher Nolan", "genre": "Psychological Thriller", "where_to_watch": "Amazon Prime, Apple TV+"}', 4),
(2, 'Donnie Darko', 'A troubled teenager is visited by a man in a rabbit suit who tells him the world will end in 28 days.', 'Time travel, parallel universes, and teenage angst. The ambiguity and symbolism give you plenty to think about during and after. Cannabis enhances the dreamlike atmosphere.', '{"year": 2001, "director": "Richard Kelly", "genre": "Sci-Fi Drama", "where_to_watch": "Amazon Prime, Apple TV+"}', 5),
(2, 'Arrival', 'A linguist is recruited to communicate with alien visitors and learn their true purpose on Earth.', 'The non-linear time concept becomes intuitive when you''re in the right mindset. The emotional payoff hits like a truck when you understand how time works for the aliens.', '{"year": 2016, "director": "Denis Villeneuve", "genre": "Sci-Fi Drama", "where_to_watch": "Paramount+, Amazon Prime"}', 6),
(2, 'Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind', 'A couple undergoes a procedure to erase each other from their memories after their relationship ends.', 'Love, loss, and memory collide in this surreal journey. Cannabis makes the emotional beats land harder and the memory manipulation sequences more immersive.', '{"year": 2004, "director": "Michel Gondry", "genre": "Romantic Sci-Fi", "where_to_watch": "Peacock, Amazon Prime"}', 7),
(2, 'Primer', 'Two engineers accidentally discover time travel in their garage and struggle with the consequences.', 'The most scientifically accurate time travel movie is also the most confusing. You''ll need a diagram afterward, but the puzzle is part of the fun when elevated.', '{"year": 2004, "director": "Shane Carruth", "genre": "Sci-Fi Thriller", "where_to_watch": "Amazon Prime, Apple TV+"}', 8),
(2, 'Shutter Island', 'A U.S. Marshal investigates a missing patient at a hospital for the criminally insane on a remote island.', 'The twist is legendary, but the journey there is a paranoid fever dream. Cannabis amplifies the unreliable narrator experience and Gothic atmosphere.', '{"year": 2010, "director": "Martin Scorsese", "genre": "Psychological Thriller", "where_to_watch": "Paramount+, Amazon Prime"}', 9),
(2, 'Predestination', 'A temporal agent embarks on his final mission to stop an elusive terrorist known as the "Fizzle Bomber."', 'Time travel paradoxes that will twist your brain into knots. The less you know going in, the better. Cannabis helps you accept the impossible logic.', '{"year": 2014, "director": "The Spierig Brothers", "genre": "Sci-Fi Thriller", "where_to_watch": "Netflix, Amazon Prime"}', 10);
